        Florence says, "Trap them in the gaps."

        Remedy replies, "Exactly — they break through the first barrier expecting another barrier, and instead encounter chemical attack."

        Florence asks, "What's your production capacity?"

        Remedy replies, "Limited — I'm depleted from yesterday. But if I focus resources on three concentrated aggressive deployments instead of broad defensive coverage…"

        Florence, working through the logistics, asks, "Which positions do you think they'll target?"

        Remedy pauses, considering, then says, "Eastern wall — they focused there yesterday. Northern approach — they avoided it before, might try it now assuming we're not defended there. And southwest — if Runner's intelligence is correct about their interest."

        Florence reminds them, "Northwest will be the false target because of Runner's misdirection."

        Remedy suggests, "Then northwest too — let them think they found a weakness, and hit them hard when they commit to attacking it."

        Florence calculates quickly, "Four zones — can you produce enough for four concentrated deployments?"

        Remedy replies, "Barely — if I start now and focus all resources on production."

        Florence orders, "*Do it.* And coordinate with Velvet on exact positions."

        Remedy shifts toward Velvet and they begin discussing placement details directly — without Florence mediating.

        Holloway moves closer to me and says softly, "This is different."

        I agree, "Yeah."

        Holloway says thoughtfully, "Yesterday Florence commanded and we followed because we had to. Today she's…"
        I finish, "Listening — incorporating — collaborating."

        Holloway says, "It's disorienting. I expected… I don't know — control, authority — not this."

        I suggest, "Not empowerment?"

        Holloway's fruiting bodies shift as they ask, "Is that what this is?"

        I say, "She asked Runner for recommendations — she told Velvet their plan was better than hers — she's letting Remedy decide deployment positions — she's not controlling, she's enabling."

        Holloway replies, "That doesn't erase what she did before."

        I acknowledge, "No — but it's still worth noticing."

        Scout bounces softly against Holloway's base. Holloway's bioluminescence flickers warmer for a moment.

        Florence is coordinating now — Velvet's barrier gaps, Remedy's chemical traps, Runner's underground misdirection — but it's not commands; it's discussion, people contributing and Florence integrating their ideas into a cohesive strategy.

        Florence asks, "Kira, where will you position during the attack?"

        Kira says, "Wherever Scout and I are safest."

        Florence says, "Central core, behind Velvet's third barrier layer — Remedy's chemical traps will be between layers two and three; you'll have maximum protection there."

        Kira asks, "What if they break through all three layers?"

        Florence says confidently, "*They won't.*"
